description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM/SECONDMENT UNTIL 31/03/2021 TO MEET THE NEEDS OF THE SERVICE.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN APPLYING FOR THE SECONDMENT POSITION, YOU MUST OBTAIN PERMISSION FROM YOUR CURRENT LINE MANAGER PRIOR TO APPLYING FOR THIS POST. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is part of the UHB’s response to COVID-19 and the wider Welsh Government’s Track, Trace the Protect project. This is an exciting secondment or fixed term (until end March 2021) opportunity has arisen for Administration Assistants to support our Population Testing Units.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This is an important role in a high profile team, key to the successful local delivery of the Track, Trace, Protect project. We are looking for an enthusiastic and highly motivated individuals to join our team. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Administrative Assistants will be part of our Testing Team, and will assist with providing a comprehensive and effective administration service. You will work in a team environment to meet the service demands and you will be required to input data into various systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 9th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Chris Padmore, Office Manager&lt;br /&gt;christopher.padmore@wales.nhs.uk&lt;br /&gt;01443 443443 ext 75683&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sian Flower&lt;br /&gt;Office Manager&lt;br /&gt;sian.flower@wales.nhs.uk&lt;br /&gt;01443 443443 ext 74897&lt;/p&gt;
